over 14 days. Each dot represents a set of reported emotion
instances. Using bodily signals recorded at the time of each report,
we ran a mathematical clustering algorithm to assign each report to
the best fitting physiological pattern (A, B, C, D, E, or unclustered).
Larger dots signify more reported emotion instances.
